&lt;NEW&gt;

The cave-like earthy smell of the tunnel was begining to die back as
noses and olfactory sensors began to adjust for it, but there was
still the feeling of moisture in the air, one of dank humidity. Not
enough to worry anyone, but enough to remind anyone in the tunnel that
above them was a rather large lake, one that could easily crush any of
them should it come down around them.

&quot;Well you tell me?&quot; WOLFGANG transmitted to NIGHTSHIFT. &quot;You are on
the outside of the base trying to get in and the door is locked, where
would you put the one switch that could disable the security holding
the door?&quot;

There was humor in WOLFGANG&#39;s voice, but what he was saying was
obvious: No one would put a kill switch on this side of the door
because then anyone could simply pull it and enter without needing the
passcodes.

However having said all that the locking mechanism on the door clicked
once and then turned and the door began to swing open.

